  </nav>
  <main>
    <article id="gta1">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto (1997)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e4/Grand_Theft_Auto_cover.png" alt="GTA 1 cover" />
      <p>The original top-down game that started it all. Released in 1997, it let players explore Liberty City, Vice City, and San Andreas. It laid the foundation for the series with its open-world chaos and crime-based missions.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="gta2">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto 2 (1999)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f0/Grand_Theft_Auto_2_cover.jpg" alt="GTA 2 cover" />
      <p>Set in a futuristic city, GTA 2 added gang warfare and more complex gameplay. While it kept the top-down view, it enhanced AI behavior and allowed players to choose sides among gangs.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="gta3">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto III (2001)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5c/Grand_Theft_Auto_III_cover.png" alt="GTA 3 cover" />
      <p>A revolutionary title that brought the franchise into 3D. Set in Liberty City, GTA III offered an immersive open-world experience with a full storyline, voice acting, and realistic physics.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="vc">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto: Vice City (2002)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/97/Grand_Theft_Auto_Vice_City_box_cover.jpg" alt="Vice City cover" />
      <p>Vice City delivered a 1980s Miami aesthetic, packed with neon, palm trees, and a rocking soundtrack. Tommy Vercetti’s rise in the drug empire gave players an unforgettable storyline and open-world fun.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="sa">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas (2004)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c4/GTASABOX.jpg" alt="San Andreas cover" />
      <p>One of the largest games of its time, San Andreas introduced CJ, gang dynamics, RPG mechanics, and a huge map with three cities. It became a cultural milestone for open-world gaming.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="gta4">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto IV (2008)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/33/Grand_Theft_Auto_IV_cover.jpg" alt="GTA 4 cover" />
      <p>Following the story of Niko Bellic in a gritty, realistic Liberty City, GTA IV focused on narrative depth and emotional storytelling, using Rockstar’s new RAGE engine for physics and animation.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="gta5">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto V (2013)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a5/Grand_Theft_Auto_V.png" alt="GTA 5 cover" />
      <p>Featuring three protagonists (Michael, Franklin, and Trevor), GTA V is one of the most successful games of all time. Its massive world, heist missions, and GTA Online made it a modern classic.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="gta6">
      <h2>Grand Theft Auto VI (TBA)</h2>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/21/Grand_Theft_Auto_VI_logo.svg/1920px-Grand_Theft_Auto_VI_logo.svg.png" alt="GTA 6 logo" />
      <p>GTA VI is currently in development and expected to be set in Vice City with dual protagonists. It promises a dynamic open world and expanded interactivity, aiming to redefine the sandbox genre once again.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
